# Design System — mirror ybala-customer-app

Source of truth: `/Users/yeasirarafat/projects/ybala-customer-app`.
Read `ybala-customer-app/CODEBASE_REFERENCE.md` before building any UI.

The user must not be able to tell this is a different app from the customer app:
same design language, spacing, typography, colors, and interaction patterns.

## Reuse the same patterns / components

- `components/Screen.tsx` — base screen wrapper for every screen
- `components/Header.tsx` — app header
- `components/CustomTabBar.tsx` — bottom tab bar
- `components/ui/` primitives: `Button`, `Input`, `Avatar`, `Badge`, `IconButton`,
  `DropdownMenu`, `Skeleton`, `Slider` (import from `components/ui`)

When a component already exists in the customer app, port it over instead of writing
a new one, keeping the same props and styling.

## Same stack / method

- **Styling:** NativeWind (Tailwind for RN), `className` props, class-based dark mode
- **Client state:** Zustand, one store per domain in `store/` (e.g. `auth.store.ts`)
- **Server state:** TanStack React Query hooks in `hooks/`
- **HTTP:** Axios services in `services/`, split into `publicApi` / `protectedApi`

## Typography & color

Typography, spacing, and colors must match the customer app. The color palette
source of truth is `ybala-customer-app/tailwind.config.js`:
primary green `#6FA25F`, secondary orange `#F38744`. Keep this repo's
`tailwind.config.js` in sync with it.
